        "subject": "LU-9398 mgc: Prevent connection invalidation on mgc",
        "message": "LU-9398 mgc: Prevent connection invalidation on mgc\n\nThis patch prevents errors when mounting more than one file system\nsimultaneously from a single MGS.  One mount thread creates the\ninitial MGC while the other waits on a mutex but after the mutex\nis released another mount thread can acquire the mutex and will\ninvalidate the MGC import connections even though they are still\nin the connecting state.  This causes an error to be returned for\nthe mount.  Instead make sure MGC imports in the connecting state\nare not invalidated until at least one attempt has been made.\n\nSigned-off-by: Jeremy Filizetti <jeremy.filizetti@gmail.com>\nChange-Id: Ia544d3e1d84b2886269beb6c82cde500c39d1b76\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
